se.jguru.nazgul.core.reflection.api.types

Class SerializableVoid

  • java.lang.Object
    • se.jguru.nazgul.core.reflection.api.types.SerializableVoid
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable

    public final class SerializableVoid
extends Object
implements Serializable

    Type definition to be used whenever java.lang.Void is desired, but a Serializable instance must be provided. An example of this situation is prevalent in clustering, when generic methods are specified to return a value. If void is desired as a return value, use this SerializableVoid class instead:

         public interface SomeActorDefinition<T extends Serializable> extends Serializable {
         T perform();
     }

    If we desire a concrete implementation of the SomeActorDefinition, which should not return a value from the perform method (which would require much more resources than a fully asynchronous call returning void) we must declare the implementation thus:

         public class AConcreteActor implements SomeActorDefinition<SerializableVoid> {
         public SerializableVoid perform() {
             // Do something
             return null;
         }
     }
    The SerializableVoid class can not be instantiated.
    Author:
    Lennart Jörelid, jGuru Europe AB
